channel.title: Name Question
channel.description:
Alright, I'm having some trouble here with names. So I was going to take some opinions from the members:
I'm going to program a Project-Insanity, and I don't know what I was going to call it. I was thinking of calling it Bronze Age as I called my Deltascape base. Then again, I was thinking of something like calling it: Bronze Age Rebirth, Bronze Age Reborn or something, I have no idea!
So.. Yeah, I'm going to need a opinion on whether or not to keep the Bronze Age name, or name it something else. It would also help to give me a few ideas for names.
Thanks,
James

item.title: Name Question
item.dc:creator: @k0_twin k0 twin
item.description:
@k0_twin wrote:

[quote=“drubrkletern, post:12, topic:373857”][quote author=k0 twin link=topic=469852.msg3435564#msg3435564 date=1292733978]

heres what ive thought up over looking through different servers:
if your name has n X in it example Crapscape, which has no clipping whatsoever, overkill of polies, no content, boring, and absolutely nothing to do, no one would play it
If its name was CrapscapeX, it would have around 500 players a day, im not sure, but thats what ive developed, because there are so many good servers out there, but dont have X in their name, but every server ive seen with X in its name, became successful, i tried them out, and they are pieces of crap servers, but only because they have X in their name
Thats the theory ive developed, so whatever your name will be, it must have an X in it (not saying yours will be crappy, but alot of people joined others servers, i even questioned them, because it has X in its name!)

I don’t understand your logic.
[/quote]

Let me shorten this down for you…
if a horrible server with the mentioned features has no X in its name (Crapscape) no one will join it, but ive noticed many servers with, lets assume Crapscape X or CrapscapeX, have tons of people, but horrible to no features at all.
My point:
For some reason, ive noticed servers with X in their name are more successful for some odd reason, even though i tried some out and they absolutely sucked, imo however.[/quote]

Sounds like a coincidence.

Read full topic
